commText: Saha and Shubman Gill are at the crease. Saha is on strike. Chahar will open the attack
Chahar to Saha, no run, full and a hint of outswing on this on off, dug out to mid-off. Was almost yorker length
Chahar to Saha, no run, short of length and tight on off, Saha jams the bat down to defend to point
Chahar to Saha, no run, back of a length outside off, Saha punches with a horizontal bat to backward point
Chahar to Saha, no run, wide of the crease and back of a length outside off, dabbed to backward point and that's four dots in a row
Chahar to Saha, 1 run, good length outside off, Saha opens the face of the bat and runs it down to third man and Saha is away
Hitting first ball in IPL career for a six Rob Quiney Kevon Cooper Andre Russell Carlos Brathwaite Aniket Choudhary Javon Searles Siddesh Lad Mahesh Theekshana Sameer Rizvi

Chahar to Shubman Gill, SIX, Shubman Gill with a tremendous shot. Vijay Shankar and Kane Williamson have wry smiles on their faces, first ball, he comes down the track, holds his shape, lofts the fullish delivery straight down the ground and it flies all the way

A change of ball. Another brand new-ball and it will be taken by Mustafizur. That's why a delay in play. A wide slip in too.
Mustafizur Rahman, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack

Mustafizur to Saha, FOUR, superb shot. Mustafizur starts with a half-volley on off, Saha gets forward and drives it with a high elbow, mid-off did not dive as he went to his right, that's a copybook shot
Mustafizur to Saha, 1 run, full outside off, Saha drives away from the body, thick inside-edge runs away wide of leg-stump and to deep backward square leg

Rashid Khan conceding 10+ runs in each over of a spell in an IPL match \n0/44 off 3 overs (16, 13, 15) vs CSK Ahmedabad 2023 (final) \n2/49 off 4 overs (11, 10, 13, 15) vs CSK Chennai 2024
Mustafizur to Shubman Gill, 1 run, fullish on off, defended to the right of backward point and it's a quick single taken despite the fielder being Jadeja
Mustafizur to Saha, FOUR, right between Dhoni and wide slip. Full and angling away from Saha who throws the bat, thick outside-edge flies away, no chance for either fielder
Mustafizur to Saha, no run, fullish and shaping away from outside off, Saha gets forward to punch on the rise, misses, flies to Dhoni
Chahar to Shubman Gill, 1 run, slower ball full and it's the leg-cutter outside off, Shubman Gill defends wide of extra-cover and the initial call was no, but then takes an easy single
Chahar to Saha, FOUR, off-pace slower ball and it's the leg-cutter outside off again, Saha comes down the track and lofts, one hand comes off but still good enough to clear mid-off
Chahar to Saha, FOUR, this is poor bowling. Taking the pace off, short of length and sits up near the tummy, Saha swivels to pull wide of deep backward square leg, one bounce over the ropes
Chahar to Saha, wide, full and down leg, Saha flicks and misses, wide called
Chahar to Saha, 1 run, fullish outside off, Saha punches and gets it wide of the diving point to his left
Given out LBW. Shubman Gill reviews. Looks plumb. No bat. Three reds and gone.
Chahar to Shubman Gill, THATS OUT!! Lbw!!

Chahar to Shubman Gill, out Lbw!! Poor shot and an even worse review. Shubman Gill swipes across the line to a thigh-high slower ball on a short of length, misses, rapped on the back leg, no bat and it's three reds. Gill takes a review with him as well. Shubman Gill lbw b Chahar 8(5) [6s-1]
Gill vs D Chahar (IPL) 56 balls 79 runs Four dismissals Avg 19.75 SR 141.07
GT Impact Player - Sai Sudharsan in, Mohit Sharma out.
Sai Sudharsan, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Chahar to Sai Sudharsan, no run, dug in short as Sai Sudharsan takes a step or two forward down the track, then sways away and leaves it to Dhoni
Tushar Deshpande, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Tushar Deshpande to Saha, 1 run, full outside off, Saha gets forward and drives nicely wide of the diving cover, but mid-off gets across and cuts it off
Tushar Deshpande to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, short of length down leg, Sai Sudharsan flicks to deep backward square leg
Tushar Deshpande to Saha, no run, slower ball off-cutter on a length on off, Saha hacks and the thick inside-edge hits the leg and rolls back to Tushar Deshpande
Tushar Deshpande to Saha, 1 run, fullish on off, driven to mid-off and Saha takes on Rutu and makes it, and there's no direct-hit either, Saha was in anyway
Tushar Deshpande to Sai Sudharsan, no run, short of length and tight on off, punched to extra-cover
Tushar Deshpande to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, slower ball full outside off, Sai Sudharsan gets forward to drive wide of mid-off for one
Chahar to Sai Sudharsan, wide, short of length down leg, Sai Sudharsan pulls and misses, wide called
Chahar to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, short on the stumps, Sai Sudharsan mistimes the pull but no square leg

Chahar to Saha, no run, my word! That has hit Saha on the helmet and the ricochet goes to cover. Good to see Saha smiling. The physio rushes out. Saha swivels to pull but is rushed by the short ball, hit him around the right ear and it was a firm blow too
The concussion protocol follows.
Chahar to Saha, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Chahar to Saha, out Caught by Tushar Deshpande!! Straight to deep square leg. A length delivery on the stumps, Saha swipes it well but it's flat and straight to Deshpande who takes it easily. Chahar punches the air and Saha shakes his head before he walks off. Saha c Tushar Deshpande b Chahar 21(17) [4s-4]
Vijay Shankar, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Chahar to Shankar, no run, short of length just outside off, Shankar punches and it's a thick inside-edge to mid-wicket
Chahar to Shankar, no run, good sharp short ball at Shankar who is quick to sway away and let it go
Chahar to Shankar, 1 run, Shankar gives the charge and this is a short of length delivery outside off, defended wide of backward point for one
Highlights (Overs 1-5) * Saha and Gill start off with a flurry of boundaries * Chahar traps Gill lbw for 8 * Runs slow down after Gill’s dismissal * Saha struck on the helmet, holes out next ball
Tushar Deshpande to Shankar, no run, short of length outside off, punched back
Tushar Deshpande to Shankar, SIX, what a blow. A short of length delivery outside off, Shankar gets into position so quickly and pulls it way over deep mid-wicket, just rose around his ribs
Tushar Deshpande to Shankar, no run, fullish and tight on off, Shankar gets forward to defend it solidly, back to Tushar Deshpande

Mitchell to Shankar, out Caught by Dhoni!! Mitchell strikes. The move to go to him has worked. Fine diving catch to his right as well by Dhoni. He takes it and gets up with a smile. Chepauk goes mental. Full around off, no feet as Shankar drives and the thick outside-edge flies, Dhoni has to dive and is airborne when he takes it with two hands. 23:27 Local Time, 17:57 GMT, 23:27 IST: Easy win for CSK. The chase never got going once Gill fell early and it was a stroll in the park for the home side after that. Sai Sudharsan after a start just couldn't hit the ball to the boundary and CSK just tightened the noose around him. Miller was the dangerman but he fell to a good catch and that was the game done at that stage. The last 6-7 overs was a mere formality as GT never looked like threatening the target. All the bowlers chipped in and it was an easy day at the office for CSK. Stay tuned for the presentation...
Biggest defeats for Titans by runs 63 runs vs CSK Chennai 2024 27 runs vs MI Mumbai WS 2023 15 runs vs CSK Chennai 2023

Shubman Gill | GT captain: They outplayed us when we were batting, their execution was spot on. We backed ourselves to get a decent score in the powerplay and once we didn’t, we were always playing catch-up. It was unfortunate for us. In T20 you can always talk about 10-15 runs here or there, end of the day it’s about how much they got. On this wicket, we were expecting to chase 190-200. I think it’s a great learning for the bowlers. I think it’s better to have this kind of game early on in the tournament rather than in the middle or late. We always expected to chase 190-200, it was a really good wicket. Felt like we let ourselves down while batting. (On captaincy) Lot of new learnings, new experiences and different things. It’s exciting to captain a team like Gujarat Titans, we’ve made it to the finals in the last couple of years so very exciting.

Deepak Chahar: Since the time I have been playing, I have been bowling 3 overs in the powerplay, used to it, just trying to bowl as well as possible with the new rules around. Earlier, if you bowled a bouncer in the first 2-3 balls, batters were always ready for a full length ball, but this new rule with two bouncers allowed in an over, it helps all the pacers. There's bounce always, but there's not much dew around at the moment. The ball grips and bounces in such conditions. I got to look at Mahi (MSD) bhai and at Ruturaj - both of them these days (for instructions.)

Ruturaj Gaikwad | CSK captain: Definitely today's game was perfect - batting, bowling and fielding, and against a team like Gujarat we needed to come up with a performance like this. In Chennai we are not sure how the wicket will be, we need to do well irrespective of batting or bowling first. Here if we have wickets in hand at the end it helps. Personally felt, Rachin batted brilliantly in the powerplay and took the game away. From there we were always ahead. [on Dube] In terms of confidence, the management and Mahi bhai worked with him personally, his confidence is very high. He knows his roles very well. Definitely he is a big plus for us. I'm impressed with the fielding as well. Maybe one or two youngsters we have extra this year and great effort from Jinks, even in the last game he was running from one end to the other. Fielding is a big tick for us.

Shivam Dube | Player of the Match: This franchise is different from all others. This franchise is giving me the freedom and I also want to win some matches for them. I worked in that way as well - it is helping me, I know they are going to bowl short balls and I'm ready for that. They want me to go on a higher strike-rate and I want to do that.

So the CSK train continues along at home in a winning way. On that note we wind up our coverage for tonight. Tomorrow we will be back with more IPL action. Do join us then. Until then, sleep tight and cuddle well. See you tomorrow.
